# Friction Log — <project-name>

Running list of moments where the skills package failed you. Don't fix mid-project — just capture. Process during the end-of-project refinement ritual.

## Format

One line per friction. Include enough context to remember what happened. Tag with the suspected skill or category.

```
- [DATE] [tag] <one-line description of what went wrong>
```

Tags can be:
- `[missing-skill]` — no skill addressed this
- `[vague-skill]` — skill existed but wasn't sharp enough
- `[skill-conflict]` — two skills gave contradictory guidance
- `[skill-overhead]` — skill applied but cost more than it saved
- `[agent-drift]` — agent ignored or worked around a skill

---

## Entries

(Add as you go. Don't worry about organizing — process happens later.)

- [2026-MM-DD] [missing-skill] <example: implementer added retry-with-backoff the plan didn't ask for; no skill against scope creep on infrastructure code>
- [2026-MM-DD] [vague-skill] <example: defensive-defaults says "timeouts on external calls" but didn't catch the missing DB query timeout>
- [2026-MM-DD] [skill-conflict] <example: boring-tech said SQLite, but spec required multi-process write; need a "when not to" branch>
- ...

---

## Processed?

- [ ] Each entry reviewed during end-of-project refinement
- [ ] Actionable items copied into retrospective's "Friction log review" section
- [ ] Noise/one-offs marked or deleted
